Colonies on solid medium usually have a typical fried-egg appearance.</s><s>Chemoorganotroph.</s><s>Ferments glucose and mannose.</s><s>Arginine, esculin, and urea are not hydrolyzed.</s><s>Reduces tetrazolium chloride.</s><s>Does not produce films and spots on egg yolk agar.</s><s>Possesses phosphatase activity.</s><s>Lyses and adsorbs bovine, ovine, and rabbit erythrocytes.</s><s>Cholesterol or serum is required for growth.</s><s>The optimum growth temperature is 37Â°C.</s><s>The G+C content of the DNA is 27.6 mol%.</s><s>Strains of <i>M. crocodyli</i> were isolated from joints and lungs of crocodiles with excudative polyarthritis.</s><s>Pathogenicity has been proved by experimental infection.</s><s>The type strain is strain MP145 (= ATCC 51981), which originated from the joint of a diseased crocodile.</s></p></content></protolog>